M(s)N(s)=I
 \begin{split} I=&(M+\delta M)(N+\delta N)=MN+M\,\delta N+\delta M\,N\\ &\implies M\,\delta N=-\delta M\,N=-\delta N\,M^{-1}\\ &\implies \delta N=-M^{-1}\,\delta M\,M^{-1}.\\ \end{split} 
 0=I'=(MN)'=M'N+MN'\implies N'=-M^{-1}\,N'\,M^{-1}. 
